comment:
I agree that she shouldn't be fired for reasons pertaining solely to her personal life. Whether someone shows up, on time, ready, willing, and able to do the job she's been hired for, that's all an employer should care about. I probably won't watch Aquaman 2, but that's because I'm boycotting Warner Bros. over the _firing_ of an actor, over strictly non-professional reasons. And also because it'll probably suck, which isn't entirely unrelated to Heard, but has no connection to where she goes poo.

About her getting fired over weight, though...
Not all decisions in Hollywood are made by "Hollywood". I imagine that everyone on set is insured by the studio, and that the insurance for leading actors is very high. The insurance company will want to be certain that anyone they're insuring against accidents, with potentially enormous pay out, are as physically capable as the risks require. While an actor can be replaced by stunt doubles in most dangerous scenes, they'll still be in scenes with a higher than normal risk, and a movie set is a pretty chaotic and dangerous place to begin with. The thing about actuaries is that they don't give a shit about political correctness. They only care about minimizing the probability of having to pay out. If they've said "Heard needs to be in THIS physical shape, or no insurance", then Heard needs to be in this physical shape, or no movie -- unless she's replaced. If she isn't on schedule to be in that shape, the producers will, at a minimum, have to prepare for a short notice replacement, i.e. investigate which suitable actors will or may be free and willing to step in.

Also, actuators make for excellent cover. "There was nothing we could do; the nerd said 'the stochastic model predicted a non-standard probability of an unacceptable adverse effect on the predictive value of the actuarial table for 35 year old women on set, so fire fucking Heard, or else', and that was that. We never figured out what the former meant, so there was no arguing with the latter. We considered giving him an atomic wedgie, but he said he was insured against that". If journalists try to get an explanation from an actuary, their eyes will start glazing over within the first minute, and they'll be dead from boredom within five. They'll have no choice but to flee for their lives, and confirm that, indeed, actuaries aren't to be messed with.

comment:
What a click-bait title, bro. I thought you were better than that. At least change it to "could face 3 years". "Faces 3 years" would mean she's already been found guilty and is waiting on sentencing.

I don't think people wanting Heard gone but being pissed about Miss Carano are hypocritical. There's substantial evidence she broke actual laws and clearly did her best to ruin Depp's reputation. That is an order of magnitude worse than posting even the most heinous shit on social media. 

Before you attack me, I don't think Gina said or posted anything worthy of being canceled, Hell, she didn't even post anything I disagree with, but even if she DID actually post anti-Semitic statements (she didn't) and said there was wide spread voter fraud (she didn't), and was an anti-masker (she isn't), and is an anti-vaxxer (she never said she was) then comparing her firing to Heard's still isn't apples to apples.

For the record, though, I do think there was wide spread voter fraud, and more and more evidence piles up every day. Just go read the Time article about "securing" the election. They admit violating the constitution to change laws to make it easier for Biden to win. I am an anti-masker, because the way the public uses masks is not effective and will never be effective, that's scientifically proven. I would also rather just be given live Covid-19 and take my chances and be isolated for two weeks or whatever than take the vaccine. So maybe I'm a little biased on whether or not Miss Carano deserves being canceled.

comment:
I've been praying my Pagan ass off for Amber to get fired. I don't give a fuck what the reason is. I personally don't believe that the "health and safety clause" is the reason at the moment.

Jeremy ALL actor's and actress's have a "health and safety clause"(the you better look the part we hired you for clause). This is far more nuanced and complex then "a few pounds overweight". It is completely legal and put into use regularly. The difference between all other movies and Aquaman 2 is the litigation with Johnny Depp and how much the public hates her. However IMPROBABLE it sounds, it is POSSIBLE. Amber Heard was hired to look a specific way and do specific things for her role. If Amber's personal lifestyle has made Amber unable to fulfill her contracted role to portray as Mira then WB and DC have every right to fire her. Amber Heard is no where near popular enough with the public, has the acting chops, or powerful within Hollywood to have the clout to keep her safe from the studio's.


One example of the more public spotlight of the clause being used for leverage against an actor is Batman and Robert Patterson. The director has been on the verge of firing him because Robert has chosen not to get into shape to play Batman.

comment:
Many celebrities have to stay fit or and get their body into shape for specific roles in films, sometimes they need to look muscular, slim, sometimes they put on the pounds to play a more overweight character. It's nothing new.

Chris Hemsworth worked out and had a tailored diet to play the godly character Thor.
Chris Pratt, lost weight and put on muscle to play Starlord in Guardians Of The Galaxy.
Natalie Portman got fit for the role of Black Swan and I bet she's training for her role as Mighty Thor in Thor 4. 
Charlize Theron gained weight for the film Monster. Look how amazingly in shape she was in the recent Netflix film The Old Guard.

If it's true that AH has breached her contractual obligations to be at a certain level of fitness to play the DC super character Mera, its well within WB's rights to recast the role with someone better suited to the character they envision. It really just depends if there is enough time to get back into shape for the role. I've no idea when they plan to start shooting.
